# Project Structure & Architecture

## Core Structure

This is a Next.js 14 App Router project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, and feature-based architecture.

### Directory Organization

```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router pages (routing only)
├── features/              # Feature-based modules (business logic)
├── shared/                # Shared components, hooks, utils, anything can share between features, modules
├── config/                # Application configuration
├── contracts/             # Smart contract ABIs and utilities
├── store/                 # Redux store (use sparingly)
└── types/                 # Global TypeScript definitions
```

## Feature-Based Architecture

Each feature should follow this structure:

```
features/
└── [feature-name]/
    ├── index.tsx                    # Feature entry point (barrel export)
    ├── [feature-name]-page.tsx      # Main page component
    ├── components/                  # Feature-specific components
    │   └── [component-name]/        # Component folder structure (ALWAYS)
    │       ├── index.tsx            # Main component implementation
    │       ├── [sub-component].tsx  # Sub-component (if complex)
    │       └── [component].types.ts # Component-specific types (if complex)
    ├── hooks/                       # Feature-specific hooks
    │   ├── use-[hook-name].ts
    │   └── index.ts                 # Barrel export
    ├── contexts/                    # React Context for non-form state
    │   └── [feature]-context.tsx
    ├── services/                    # API calls and business logic
    │   ├── [service-name].service.ts
    │   └── index.ts
    ├── types/                       # Feature TypeScript types (directory)
    │   ├── index.ts                 # Barrel export
    │   ├── [type-group].types.ts    # Grouped types
    │   └── [another-group].types.ts
    ├── schemas/                     # Zod validation schemas (directory)
    │   ├── index.ts                 # Barrel export
    │   └── [form-name].schema.ts    # Individual schemas
    └── constants/                   # Feature constants (directory)
        ├── index.ts                 # Barrel export
        └── [group].constants.ts     # Grouped constants
```

## File Organization Rules

### CRITICAL: Directory-Based Pattern

**ALWAYS use directories for scalability, even for single files:**

#### Components
**✅ CORRECT - index.tsx is the main component:**
```
components/
└── hero-section/
    └── index.tsx              # Main component implementation

# If complex, add sub-components:
components/
└── hero-section/
    ├── index.tsx              # Main component
    ├── hero-content.tsx       # Sub-component
    └── hero-image.tsx         # Sub-component
```

**❌ INCORRECT - Never single file:**
```
components/
└── hero-section.tsx  # Hard to scale later
```

**Component File Pattern:**

**Simple Component** (most cases):
```
components/button/
└── index.tsx          # Contains the Button component
```

**Complex Component** (when needed):
```
components/data-table/
├── index.tsx          # Main DataTable component
├── table-header.tsx   # Sub-component
├── table-row.tsx      # Sub-component
├── table-pagination.tsx # Sub-component
└── types.ts           # Component-specific types
```

**Why index.tsx as main file?**
- ✅ Start simple with just `index.tsx`
- ✅ Add sub-components in same folder if needed
- ✅ No need to refactor exports - just add files
- ✅ Clean imports: `import { Button } from './button'`
- ✅ No separate export file needed

#### Types
**✅ CORRECT - Always use directory:**
```
types/
├── index.ts                   # Barrel export
├── user.types.ts              # User-related types
└── api.types.ts               # API-related types
```

**❌ INCORRECT - Never single file:**
```
types.ts  # Hard to organize when it grows
```

#### Schemas
**✅ CORRECT - Always use directory:**
```
schemas/
├── index.ts                   # Barrel export
└── login-form.schema.ts       # Login schema
```

**❌ INCORRECT - Never single file:**
```
schemas.ts  # Hard to manage multiple forms
```

#### Constants  
**✅ CORRECT - Always use directory:**
```
constants/
├── index.ts                   # Barrel export
├── api.constants.ts           # API constants
└── validation.constants.ts    # Validation constants
```

**❌ INCORRECT - Never single file:**
```
constants.ts  # Gets too long quickly
```

### Why Directories Always?

- ✅ **Future-proof**: Easy to add new files without refactoring
- ✅ **Organized**: Related code stays together
- ✅ **500-line limit**: Never hit the limit per file
- ✅ **Scalable**: Grows naturally with the project
- ✅ **Clear imports**: Barrel exports keep imports clean

### Routing

- `app/` directory is for routing ONLY
- Page components should import from `features/`
- Keep route files minimal (< 50 lines)

**Example:**
```typescript
// app/borrow/page.tsx
import { BorrowPage } from '@/features/borrow/borrow-page';

export default function BorrowRoute() {
  return <BorrowPage />;
}
```

## File Size Limits

- **Maximum 500 lines per file**
- If a file exceeds 500 lines, break it into smaller modules
- Use directory structure to organize related files
- Extract reusable logic into separate utilities

## Import Organization

```typescript
// 1. External dependencies
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';

// 2. Internal features
import { BorrowForm } from '@/features/borrow/components';

// 3. Shared components
import { Button, Card } from '@/shared/components';

// 4. Utilities and types
import { cn } from '@/shared/utils';
import type { BorrowFormData } from './types';

// 5. Styles (if any)
import './styles.css';
```

## Component Guidelines

### Export Pattern

Use named exports for components:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
export const HeroSection: React.FC<HeroProps> = ({ title }) => {
  return <section>{title}</section>;
};

// ❌ INCORRECT
export default function HeroSection({ title }) {
  return <section>{title}</section>;
}
```

### Component Organization

```typescript
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from 'react';

// 2. Types
interface Props {
  title: string;
}

// 3. Component
export const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ title }) => {
  // 4. State
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  
  // 5. Hooks
  const data = useCustomHook();
  
  // 6. Handlers
  const handleClick = () => {};
  
  // 7. Effects
  useEffect(() => {}, []);
  
  // 8. Render helpers
  const renderContent = () => {};
  
  // 9. Return JSX
  return <div>{title}</div>;
};
```

## Quick Reference

- **File limit:** 500 lines maximum
- **Component structure:** Always use directory-based organization
- **Exports:** Named exports preferred
- **State management:** Context API for features, Redux for global only
- **API calls:** React Query (TanStack Query) required
- **Hooks:** Feature-specific hooks in `features/[name]/hooks/`
